Dia. 04 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's tiger's mouth move at 1 on the right side is the\cf1\b  vital point for living\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par Against Black's cut at 2, White can live with 3. In actual game, Black is going to play at 3 instead of 2 and White lives with 2.
\par }
